Business Brief -- Fleet/Norstar Financial Group Inc.:
   Commercial Loans Totaling
   $400 Million Are Acquired
Recoll was created to liquidate about 16,000 loans, with a
face value of about $5.8 billion, that the government assumed
after the failure last year of Bank of New England, which
Fleet bought in July.
   Separately, Fleet said its Bank of New Hampshire unit
assumed $22 million in deposits of the failed Atlantic Trust
Co., in Newington, N.H., from the FDIC.